<subSubSection id="5C8171834C67D9BD70485CE43CA28242" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5F94B9FA85A00CB46A0AADE5CDE8A77E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC517E1E32329D1E8FC504877900CE07" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New record: Struma Valley, Kamenitsa vill., 31.05.-03.06.2002, pitfall traps, 3 w., leg. M. Langourov. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="F8649ACBE8B01DFBCE31CFD962CF1904" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C48350506545F347EE1F7C043F3636DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FD8DE43E62D5628EF77B17793AD17D20" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CDF8AD02301A2A6F509CF4DDB74C3A11" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
The only published record comes from the hill of Kozhuh, situated not far from the new locality. As noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="73FD4B44DABD735F6C1D1AC50AF8B09A" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Silesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 22" refId="B7725669" refString="Borowiec, L., Salata, S., 2018. New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece. Acta Entomologica Silesiana 26: 1 - 22" title="New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece" volume="26" year="2018">Borowiec and Salata (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, this species is widespread in the Balkans and Turkey.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
